cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

This paper focuses on developing a deep learning framework for a contact-event-based robotic grasping system using vision-based tactile sensors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the tactile sensor is vision-based. The paper also involves developing a neural network, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of deep learning methods, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement in robustness of the grasping system, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
